---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import CaseStudyHero from '../components/CaseStudyHero.astro';

// TODO(emily): origin story (what specific moment made you build this?),
// rough traction numbers if you want them public (hangs created, RSVP rate),
// and anything you learned that changed the product.
---

<BaseLayout
  title="HangEasy — Case Study | Emily Denis"
  description="Make plans that actually happen: a social planning tool where guests RSVP in one tap with no app and no account. PM case study by Emily Denis."
  ogImage="/images/hangeasy-hero.png"
>
  <Header backLink />

  <CaseStudyHero
    title="HangEasy"
    tagline="Case study · social coordination"
    accent="text-fuchsia-600 dark:text-fuchsia-400"
    intro="Everyone says 'we should hang.' Group texts get noisy, someone doesn't reply, the thread dies, and another month goes by. HangEasy turns intent into a locked-in plan — in two minutes, with zero friction for guests."
    facts={[
      { label: 'Role', value: 'PM · design · engineering (solo)' },
      { label: 'Status', value: 'Live at hangeasy.app' },
      { label: 'Platform', value: 'Web (no install)' },
      { label: 'Guest requirement', value: 'None — one tap' },
    ]}
    ctas={[
      { label: 'Visit hangeasy.app', href: 'https://hangeasy.app', primary: true },
    ]}
  />

  <article class="prose-custom mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pb-24">
    <h2>The problem</h2>
    <p>
      Social plans don't fail because people don't want to see each other — they fail
      because coordination overhead outlives enthusiasm. A group thread starts warm,
      collects two "maybe"s and one silence, and quietly dies. The cost isn't an app
      problem; it's a <strong>friendship maintenance</strong> problem, and it
      compounds as everyone gets busier.
    </p>

    <h2>The insight: friction is asymmetric</h2>
    <p>
      One person — the organizer — is motivated enough to do real work. Everyone else
      will give you <em>one tap</em>, on a good day. Most planning tools fail because
      they tax the guests: download an app, create an account, learn a UI. HangEasy
      puts all the work on the person who already wants to do it and makes the
      guest's job effortless:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>No app, no account, no sign-up for guests.</strong> Every hang is a shareable link; RSVP is one tap. The easier it is to respond, the more people actually do.</li>
      <li><strong>Time options, not scheduling tetris.</strong> The organizer proposes a few times and friends vote — no hunting for the single slot that magically works for everyone.</li>
      <li><strong>Vibes set expectations.</strong> Coffee run, game night, hiking — guests know what they're saying yes to before they reply.</li>
      <li><strong>A live view of who's in</strong>, and a clear moment where the plan is locked: no more "so are we actually doing this?"</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Product decisions</h2>
    <h3>SMS, not push</h3>
    <p>
      Notifications matter for a coordination product, but push requires an installed
      app — which guests explicitly don't have. SMS reaches everyone with a phone
      number, with a plain opt-out. The channel choice falls straight out of the
      zero-install constraint.
    </p>
    <h3>The confirmation moment is the product</h3>
    <p>
      Polls and threads already exist. What they lack is the state transition from
      "gauging interest" to <strong>"this is happening: Friday, 7pm, Emily's
      place."</strong> HangEasy is designed around reaching and celebrating that
      moment — everything else (vibes, votes, links) exists to get there faster.
    </p>

    <h2>What I'd measure</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Confirmation rate</strong>: share of created hangs that reach a locked-in date — the product's one number.</li>
      <li>Guest RSVP rate per share (does zero-friction actually convert?).</li>
      <li>Repeat organizers within 30 days — the habit signal.</li>
      <li>Time from hang creation to confirmation.</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="mt-12 flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="https://hangeasy.app" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary">Visit hangeasy.app ↗</a>
      <a href="/" class="btn-secondary">← All work</a>
    </div>
  </article>

  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
